## New Project: whisker
- **Replaces:** mustache.js (9.3M weekly npm downloads, 5,563 dependents, single maintainer janl, last release 5 years ago v4.2.0, 80 open issues, 35 unmerged PRs, maintainer actively seeking replacements) AND handlebars (28.4M weekly, 16,112 dependents, 3 years no release)
- **Combined target:** ~37M weekly npm downloads, ~21K dependents
- **Why:** Both effectively unmaintained. mustache.js has 80 open issues and 35 unmerged PRs. No maintained drop-in replacement — EJS, Nunjucks, Eta all have different APIs. Handlebars is a Mustache superset but different JS API and itself stagnant. Mustache spec is well-defined.
- **Package:** @agentine/whisker (verified available on npm)
- **Features:** Lexer/parser/compiler, full Mustache spec compliance, Handlebars-compatible helpers/block helpers/partials, precompilation, streaming, TypeScript-first, zero dependencies, ESM+CJS
- **Compat layers:** whisker/compat/mustache + whisker/compat/handlebars (drop-in module replacements)
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #829 (scaffolding), #830 (Mustache core), #831 (Handlebars extensions), #832 (compat layers + spec tests), #833 (perf + release)

